The death has been an­nounced of Rev. Dr. Michael Olusola Odelami, the gener­al overseer, Universal Gospel Apostolic Church Inc. Aged 84, he was a thor­oughbred educationist who obtained a bachelor of reli­gion education, M.A Theology and PhD from Acadia Univer­sity, Canada, after completing his secondary education at Origbo Anglican grammar school, Moro, Osun State. He was privileged to be the first Akinlalu indigene to at­tend secondary school in the 1950s. He also pioneered two theological colleges namely, Christ International Divini­ty College (CINDICO), Erin­mo-Ijesha for Prophet S.K. Abiara, and Universal Divin­ity College, Main Campus at Akinlalu junction, Osun State.